# {{.BinaryName}}

{{.Description}}

SoulModule plugin for Soul Stack ({{.Namespace}}.{{.Name}}). Implemented via `sdk/module` on top of the gRPC-stdio handshake ([ADR-020](https://github.com/souls-guild/soul-stack/blob/main/docs/architecture.md#adr-020-plugin-infrastructure-manifest-handshake-lifecycle-format)).

## States

- `present` - the resource exists with the requested parameters.
- `absent` - the resource is absent.

Parameters - see `manifest.yaml::spec.states.<state>.input`.

Any `secret: true` parameter must have `pattern: "^vault:.*"` - otherwise `soul-lint validate-manifest` fails with an error (semantic rule `input_secret_without_vault_pattern`).

## Usage in destiny

```yaml
- module: {{.Namespace}}.{{.Name}}
  state: present
  name: example
  # TODO: remaining params
```

## Build

```
make build       # -> bin/{{.BinaryName}}
make test
make check       # fmt + vet + test + build
```

## Sigil-trust

Before publishing an official plugin to production, an Archon signs the binary's
digest through Keeper ([ADR-026](https://github.com/souls-guild/soul-stack/blob/main/docs/architecture.md#adr-026-sigil---plugin-integrity-keeper-signed-digest-index)).

## Tests

- **L0** - unit tests with a mock `pluginv1.SoulModule_ApplyServer` (see `internal/{{.NamePackage}}/handler_test.go`).
- **L1** - integration via testcontainers against a real backend resource.
- **L3b** - real-soul-container (privileged Debian-12 + the module installed).

More details - [Plugin author guide](https://github.com/souls-guild/soul-stack-plugins/blob/main/docs/module-author-guide.md).

